Class GenericInputMethod<V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.situx.postagger.main.gui.ime.descriptor.GenericInputMethod<V>
  • Type Parameters:
    V - the parameterized input key type
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.awt.im.spi.InputMethod

    public class GenericInputMethod<V>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.awt.im.spi.InputMethod
    A two-stage InputMethod that first buffers "raw" input until the raw input amounts to an a particular key as determined by a pluggable InputTermSource. When the raw input is accepted as a key, it can then be converted into uncommitted input. The uncommitted input is added if possible as
